                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T18:52:53.241+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">《元经》以褒贬代替赏罚，是因为天下没有明主而赏罚不明啊！”薛收说：“那么《春秋》始自周平王和鲁隐公，用意也是如此了？”先生说：“是这样啊！但人们不了解这一点。”薛收说：“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.12" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T18:57:16.55+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">these were replacements for the rewards and the punishments.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T18:57:22.819+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">代替赏罚，是因为天下没有明主而赏罚不明啊！”薛收说：“那么《春秋》始自周平王和鲁隐公，用意也是如此了？”先生说：“是这样啊！但人们不了解这一点。”薛收说：“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.13" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T18:59:54.354+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Then All Under Heaven was going to have no ruler</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:00:50.368+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Since All Under Heaven was without any (proper ruler)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.14" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:03:07.711+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">rewards and punishments were surely remaining unclear!”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:03:20.613+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Since All Under Heaven being without any (enlightened ruler)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:06:46.279+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">how could rewards and punishments fail to be unenlightened.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:07:10.504+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">是因为天下没有明主而赏罚不明啊！”薛收说：“那么《春秋》始自周平王和鲁隐公，用意也是如此了？”先生说：“是这样啊！但人们不了解这一点。”薛收说：“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-12a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:08:00.288+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">而赏罚不明啊！”薛收说：“那么《春秋》始自周平王和鲁隐公，用意也是如此了？”先生说：“是这样啊！但人们不了解这一点。”薛收说：“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:11:48.008+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">“First now I understand that when there is good order in the world</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:13:05.814+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">then it is the Sage who is in charge,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:23:05.276+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Xuē Shōu said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:27:16.252+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Xuē Shōu said: "So then, the</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:28:17.16+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">用意也是如此了？”先生说：“是这样啊！但人们不了解这一点。”薛收说：“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:28:47.914+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">“那么《春秋》始自周平王和鲁隐公，</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:30:42.044+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">薛收说：</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:31:40.056+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">薛收说：“那么《春秋》始自周平王和鲁隐公，</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:31:52.562+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:32:24.603+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:32:37.209+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">“***First now I understand that when there is proper governancer in the world</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:32:43.976+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">“现在我知道了：天下太平，则圣人高居在上；天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:32:53.499+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:33:33.534+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and when there is chaos in the world</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:33:42.131+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">天下不安定，圣人则潜伏于下。圣人得志则从政施行赏罚，不得志则通过著述进行褒贬。皇极因此得到重建，人文制度因此不会沦丧。它的意义难道不深远吗？”薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:34:51.975+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">***then a Sage is in charge,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:35:14.018+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">When the Sage succeeds then rewards and punishments are properly practised;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:35:59.759+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">it is the Sage who is in an inferior position.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:37:34.791+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">the Sage succeeds then rewards and punishments are properly practised;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.8" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:39:23.568+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and when the Sage fails to win through, approbation and reprobation (in the history books) arises.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:40:36.328+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">the Sage will lie low.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:42:14.829+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">When the Sage succeeds wins through then rewards and punishments are properly assigned;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:42:39.32+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and it is when the Sage is having a hard time, that approbations and reprobations (in the history books) arises.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.9" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:43:05.749+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Then the Ultimate Imperial Order is re-established</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.10" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:45:02.693+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and this civilised pattern LYxxx is not lost.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:45:39.456+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and this civilised culture is not lost.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.11" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:46:21.984+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">That is surely a profound point!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T19:46:59.845+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and is not the the deep point of it all?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.12" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:47:51.45+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Having bowed twice he (Xuē Shōu) left</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.13" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:48:44.477+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and he reported the matter to Dǒng Cháng.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.14" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T19:49:55.677+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Dǒng Cháng said (echoing Confucius himself):</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.15" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T20:36:15.811+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">“After the death of Confucius the civilised pattern is now found here!”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T20:39:56.775+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">薛收再拜而出，向董常讲述了这件事。董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T20:40:55.962+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">to report on all this to Dǒng Cháng.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-13a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T20:41:01.795+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">董常说：“孔子死后，人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:12:43.718+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">人文之道就在先生这里了吧？”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:14:49.418+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:15:51.166+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">文中子曰：</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:16:18.289+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">“卓哉，周孔○1 之道！</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:16:32.619+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">其神之所为乎○2 ？</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:17:02.289+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">顺之则吉，逆之则凶。”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:18:02.09+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">违反它就会有凶险。”1.10</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:19:14.102+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">It (their Way)  surely is the work of a supernatural power!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:19:47.612+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">If one conforms to this way, that is auspicious;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:27:04.871+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">if one goes against that way, that is inauspicious.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:30:04.978+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">This Way surely is the work of a god:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:31:09.094+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">This Way surely is the work of a god:　　【ZP quotes a helpful passage from the</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:35:44.257+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and if one goes against that way, that is inauspicious.  【The luck-bringing cosmological dimension of the Way of the royal Founding Fathers of the Zhōu, and their follower Confucius, has been central from Hàn times onwards, and is stated explicitly here.  The Confucian teaching is not just morally right, it is cosmologically auspicious and thus concordant with Heaven.】</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:36:19.797+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">When, in the Primal Classic the Master transmitted the matter of the huángshǐ period (371-409) (unification of the area north of the Yellow River)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:37:55.614+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">he heaved a sigh on that occasion.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:38:34.861+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">His entourage did not quite understand what was going on,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:38:38.918+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">门人感到不解。王凝说：“先生是在感叹天命吧。《尚书》说天命无常，只归属有德的人。拓跋氏有德，于是百姓向往归附，三才难道会舍弃他吗？”先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.5" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:39:09.248+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">but (the Master’s younger brother) Wáng Níng commented:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:40:39.989+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">“When our Master’s sighed</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.7" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:40:56.826+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">he was presumably sighing about fate.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:41:22.775+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">《尚书》说天命无常，只归属有德的人。拓跋氏有德，于是百姓向往归附，三才难道会舍弃他吗？”先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.8" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:42:13.7+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">The Documents have it:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:42:30.062+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">《尚书》说天命无常，只归属有德的人。拓跋氏有德，于是百姓向往归附，三才难道会舍弃他吗？”先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:42:57.297+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">天命无常，只归属有德的人。拓跋氏有德，于是百姓向往归附，三才难道会舍弃他吗？”先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.9" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:44:52.62+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">“The decrees of Heaven are not mechanically constant</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.10" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:45:45.642+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">they turn only to those who are possessed of virtue.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.11" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:49:37.077+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">(Even) the virtue of the Róng and of the Dí barbarians (i.e. the barbarian rulers of the Northern Wèi and their likes)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.12" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T22:50:13.632+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">the black-haired (Chinese) people cherished/identified with it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:50:20.202+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">拓跋氏有德，于是百姓向往归附，三才难道会舍弃他吗？”先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:51:05.88+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">于是百姓向往归附，三才难道会舍弃他吗？”先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:57:23.342+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">the black-haired (Chinese) people warmly welcomed it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T22:57:41.026+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">先生听到后对王凝说：“凝，你知道天命啊！”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-15a.16" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:02:14.229+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">you do understand decreed fate!”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:05:46.406+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">When the Master was in Cháng Ān</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:06:16.759+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">Yáng Sù Yáng Sù 楊素 (died 606, poet and general, also known as “Sir” Yuè 越公, member of Wáng Tōng’s group of visitors and interlocutors), Sū Kuí (Suí official under 隋煬帝), and Lǐ Délín (Suí dynasty official, died 591) all begged for an interview.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:06:43.29+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">The Master had discussions with them</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:07:22.362+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">but when he returned he wore a worried expression on his face.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:08:24.352+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">A follower asked the Master about this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.11" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:09:38.056+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">and he discussed songs all day, but he did not get through to dignified elegance.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.2" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:10:18.093+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">The follower went on:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.3" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:11:11.321+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">“So what were you worried about?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T23:11:52.896+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">When the Master was (for an audience witht the Suí Emperor) in Cháng Ān</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T23:12:55.999+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">(the courtiers) Yáng Sù Yáng Sù 楊素 (died 606, poet and general, also known as “Sir” Yuè 越公, member of Wáng Tōng’s group of visitors and interlocutors), Sū Kuí (Suí official under 隋煬帝), and Lǐ Délín (Suí dynasty official, died 591) all begged for an interview</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T23:13:00.751+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-zh-287cbdf3">先生和他们谈话回来后面带忧色。弟子问其中缘故，先生说：“杨素和我谈话，整日只谈政事而不谈教化；苏夔和我谈话，整日只谈音律而不谈雅乐；李德林和我谈话，整日只谈虚文而不谈实理。”弟子问：“那么您忧虑什么呢？”先生说：“这不是你们能知道的。这几位都是朝廷中参与议政的人，只谈政事而不谈教化，天下就没有礼制了；只谈声律而不谈乐，天下就没有乐教了；只谈虚文而不谈治理；天下就没有文道了。这样王道如何能兴起呢？我因此而忧虑啊。”弟子退下，先生取琴弹奏《诗经·荡》，弟子们都感动得流下了眼泪。</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T23:13:46.201+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">But when he got back home, he wore a worried expression on his face.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-12-01T23:14:57.485+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">When ancolyte asked the Master about this,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.7" xml:lang="en" modified="2024-12-01T23:15:17.511+09:00" resp-del="#CH" src-id="KR3a0014-en">The Master said:</seg>
